The paper deals with the construction of involutions over finite fields, which is a topic that is relevant to several areas of computer science. In particular, involutions are widely used in cryptography and coding theory, which suggests that cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are likely sub-categories. The paper also involves algebraic techniques, which could place it in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper proposes a general method for constructing involutions, which could be relevant to cs.SD (Systems and Control).
